YOU WANT TO WEAR THAT?

08:11.403 --> 08:13.754
IT BEING ON ME IMPLIES
THAT I WANT TO WEAR IT.

08:13.797 --> 08:17.018
OKAY. I LIKE IT.

08:18.323 --> 08:19.586
WOW.

08:19.629 --> 08:21.892
A WHOLE ROOM
THAT'S A CLOSET?

08:21.936 --> 08:23.241
YOU COULD MAKE THIS
INTO A LITTLE GYM,

08:23.285 --> 08:24.547
HANG A HEAVY BAG THERE.

08:24.591 --> 08:26.114
YEAH, DANNY,
THAT'S WHAT I WANT.

08:26.157 --> 08:28.377
I WANT A BAG
FULL OF SAND TO PUNCH

08:28.420 --> 08:30.988
INSTEAD OF ALL MY CLOTHES.

08:31.032 --> 08:32.555
OKAY, WHAT ABOUT THIS ONE?
YOU LIKE THAT?

08:32.599 --> 08:34.818
LET ME GUESS: YOU WANT ME
TO WEAR A LITTLE BLACK DRESS,

08:34.862 --> 08:36.603
PUSH-UP BRA, HIGH HEELS.

08:36.646 --> 08:38.518
BORING, SEXY, ANONYMOUS GIRL.

08:38.561 --> 08:39.693
SEXY'S NOT BORING.

08:39.736 --> 08:41.216
YOU GOT ANY FOOD?
COLD CUTS?

08:41.259 --> 08:43.479
NO, BUT I THINK I HAVE
SOME PIZZA FROM ELECTION NIGHT.

08:43.523 --> 08:47.004
I THINK THIS DATE'S
GONNA BE FUN.

08:47.048 --> 08:49.746
LET'S TAKE A SHOT.
YOU LOOK NICE.

08:49.790 --> 08:51.139
THANKS.
TO...

08:51.182 --> 08:52.575
TRUE LOVE.SEX WITH NEW PEOPLE.

08:52.619 --> 08:54.011
DANNY.

08:54.055 --> 08:55.186
HEY, GUYS.

08:55.230 --> 08:56.361
HI.
HEY.

08:56.405 --> 08:57.754
LUCY, YOU REMEMBER DANNY.
DANNY, LUCY.

08:57.798 --> 08:58.755
HI, NICE TO MEET YOU.

08:58.799 --> 09:00.365
NICE TO MEET YOU.

09:00.409 --> 09:02.193
BEAUTIFUL.

09:02.237 --> 09:03.238
OH, MAN.

09:03.281 --> 09:04.805
WHAT?

09:04.848 --> 09:06.241
THAT'S A KING SALMON
OVER THERE.

09:06.284 --> 09:07.459
SO?

09:07.503 --> 09:09.026
JILLIAN STUDIED THE MIGRATION
OF THAT FISH.

09:09.070 --> 09:10.332
NO.
YEAH. THAT FISH GOES
FROM SALT WATER...

09:10.375 --> 09:11.594
NO. STOP IT.
TO FRESH WATER.

09:11.638 --> 09:13.117
IT'S AN AMAZING FISH.

09:13.161 --> 09:14.162
THEY DO IT TO MATE.NOBODY CARES.

09:14.205 --> 09:15.250
TO MATE.DANNY, NOBODY CARES.

09:15.293 --> 09:16.294
HEY.
HEY, GUYS?

09:16.338 --> 09:17.339
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

09:17.382 --> 09:18.601
REALLY GOOD.

09:18.645 --> 09:20.037
WOULD YOU MIND
SWITCHING SEATS WITH ME?

09:20.081 --> 09:21.996
BECAUSE THAT FISH
IS IN MY EYE LINE,

09:22.039 --> 09:23.475
JUST PUTTING ME IN A--

09:23.519 --> 09:25.260
A BAD PLACE EMOTIONALLY
RIGHT NOW.

09:25.303 --> 09:26.478
THE FISH?

09:26.522 --> 09:28.306
THAT ONE, YEAH.
YEAH?

09:28.350 --> 09:29.873
YEAH, SURE.
IT'S YOUR EYE LINE.DO YOU MIND?

09:29.917 --> 09:32.093
OKAY, GREAT.
THANKS.

09:32.136 --> 09:33.094
[Jamie]
WOULDN'T WANT TO LOOK

09:33.137 --> 09:34.356
AT SOMETHING
I DIDN'T LIKE.

09:34.399 --> 09:36.314
OH, YEAH, THANK YOU.
THAT'S MUCH BETTER.

09:36.358 --> 09:38.099
GOOD.

09:38.142 --> 09:41.189
SO CAN I ASK WHAT EXACTLY
YOUR PROBLEM IS

09:41.232 --> 09:42.407
WITH SEA LIFE?

09:42.451 --> 09:45.019
OH, IT'S JUST,
MY EX WAS AN OCEANOGRAPHER.

09:45.062 --> 09:46.150
IT'S STUPID.

09:46.194 --> 09:47.195
YEAH, IT IS STUPID.

09:47.238 --> 09:48.413
HEY, LOOK
AT THIS BREAD SELECTION.

09:48.457 --> 09:50.372
THERE'S WHITE BREAD. THERE'S THE BROWN BREAD.

09:50.415 --> 09:52.983
JUST IF I KEEP MYSELF
FROM SEEING TRIGGERS,

09:53.027 --> 09:54.202
THEN, YOU KNOW,

09:54.245 --> 09:55.203
I DON'T FIXATE ON HER--

09:55.246 --> 09:56.421
OW!

09:56.465 --> 09:58.032
DID SOMEBODY
JUST KICK ME?

09:58.075 --> 09:59.207
YOU OKAY? OW!

09:59.250 --> 10:00.425
[Mindy] YEAH, THAT IS SO WEIRD.

10:00.469 --> 10:01.992
I THINK THAT MAYBE
WE SHOULD MOVE TABLES,

10:02.036 --> 10:04.168
OR WE COULD TRY
NOT TALKING ABOUT EXES

10:04.212 --> 10:05.213
AND SEE
IF THE KICKING STOPS.

10:05.256 --> 10:06.344
YOU KNOW WHAT, THOUGH?

10:06.388 --> 10:08.390
I HAVE FOUND
THAT THE HARDEST BREAKUPS

10:08.433 --> 10:09.826
ARE THE ONES
WHERE YOU MIGHT HAVE

10:09.870 --> 10:11.654
UNDERESTIMATED THE PERSON
WHILE YOU WERE WITH THEM,

10:11.698 --> 10:12.873
I DON'T KNOW IF--

10:12.916 --> 10:14.657
YES. THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT I'M GOING THROUGH.

10:14.701 --> 10:16.659
REALLY?
YES.

10:16.703 --> 10:17.921
IT--IT'S LIKE YOU'RE--

10:17.965 --> 10:19.270
[laughs]
I KNOW, IT'S SO WEIRD.

10:19.314 --> 10:20.532
THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT
IS GOING ON

10:20.576 --> 10:22.273
WITH ME AND JILLIAN. NO WAY.

10:22.317 --> 10:23.666
WELL, IT WAS ME, REALLY.
I JUST--

10:23.710 --> 10:24.885
TELL ME ABOUT THAT.

10:24.928 --> 10:26.364
UH, JAMIE?
YEAH.

10:26.408 --> 10:27.322
I DON'T WANT
TO JINX THIS,

10:27.365 --> 10:29.019
BUT I THINK
MATCH-DOT-MINDY

10:29.063 --> 10:30.325
MIGHT HAVE
ANOTHER SUCCESS STORY.

10:30.368 --> 10:32.327
YOU KNOW, YOU CAN HAVE
A FRIENDSHIP, MAYBE.

10:32.370 --> 10:33.807
YEAH?

10:33.850 --> 10:35.025
SO, MORGAN,
YOU WANT TO TAKE

10:35.069 --> 10:36.418
THIS GIRL
TO THE BATTING CAGES.

10:36.461 --> 10:37.680
I'M STILL NOT SURE
WHAT THOSE ARE.

10:37.724 --> 10:39.073
THREE-PRONGED ATTACK,
MORGAN.

10:39.116 --> 10:40.944
NUMBER ONE, CASUAL APPROACH.

10:40.988 --> 10:42.076
WATCH ME, WATCH ME,
WATCH ME.

10:42.119 --> 10:43.555
WHAT AM I DOING?
WHAT AM I DOING?

10:43.599 --> 10:44.600
WHAT AM I DOING?I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE GONNA--

10:44.644 --> 10:45.993
NOW.

10:46.036 --> 10:47.298
WOW, OKAY, YOU LOOK
LIKE JOE BIDEN.

10:47.342 --> 10:48.604
THAT IS AWESOME.

10:48.648 --> 10:51.955
NUMBER TWO, INITIATE
SOME LIGHT PHYSICAL CONTACT.

10:51.999 --> 10:53.000
OKAY.
OH, RED.

10:53.043 --> 10:54.262
NICE COLOR.
OH, YEAH.

10:54.305 --> 10:55.872
IT'S VALENTINE'S DAY,
AND IT HIDES THE BLOOD.

10:55.916 --> 10:58.962
THAT'S DISGUSTING. NUMBER THREE.
OFFER HER SOMETHING SMALL.

10:59.006 --> 11:01.095
A TOKEN OF SORTS.
IT ESTABLISHES A DEBT.

11:01.138 --> 11:03.663
GOT A FREE COLA
FROM THE VENDING MACHINE.

11:03.706 --> 11:05.795
OH, I'VE ACTUALLY BEEN STARING
AT THAT THING ALL MORNING.

11:05.839 --> 11:08.015
THANKS, DOC.
I OWE YOU ONE.

11:08.058 --> 11:10.017
OH! IT'S A--
PART OF THE ROUTINE.

11:10.060 --> 11:11.235
THERE IT IS.
OKAY.

11:11.279 --> 11:12.454
IT'S THE DEBT.
I GOT IT.

11:12.497 --> 11:13.934
YOU JUST GIVE HER
WHATEVER YOU HAVE ON YOU.

11:13.977 --> 11:15.326
WHY NOT?
ALL RIGHT.

11:15.370 --> 11:16.327
SO I'LL BE LIKE,

11:16.371 --> 11:19.504
"HEY, THIS IS FOR YOU."

11:21.158 --> 11:22.333
WHERE'S THE BODY?

11:22.377 --> 11:23.813
I JUST FOUND THE HEAD
IN THE TOILET.

11:23.857 --> 11:25.119
OH, GOD.

11:25.162 --> 11:26.990
YOU NEVER KNOW
A LOVE SONG

11:27.034 --> 11:28.339
UNTIL YOU HAVE
A BROKEN HEART, RIGHT?

11:28.383 --> 11:29.732
MM, YES.

11:29.776 --> 11:31.386
AND FINALLY YOU REALIZE
THAT ALL OF THESE SONGS

11:31.429 --> 11:32.866
THAT YOU THOUGHT
WERE SO HAPPY-SOUNDING

11:32.909 --> 11:34.084
ARE ACTUALLY SO SAD.

11:34.128 --> 11:35.738
LIKE YOU CAN CALL ME AL.
MM.

11:35.782 --> 11:37.914
"WHERE IS MY WIFE
AND FAMILY?

11:37.958 --> 11:39.307
WHAT IF I DIE HERE?"

11:39.350 --> 11:41.091
WHO'LL BE MY ROLE MODEL
NOW THAT MY...
ONCE MY...

11:41.135 --> 11:42.527
[both]
ROLE MODEL'S GONE?

11:42.571 --> 11:43.964
MAN, I GOTTA DOWNLOAD
THAT ALBUM AGAIN.
MM-HMM.

11:44.007 --> 11:45.052
IT'S A GREAT ONE.

11:45.095 --> 11:46.488
I THINK THEY REALLY LIKE
EACH OTHER.

11:46.531 --> 11:47.837
WELL, THEY LIKE PAUL SIMON.

11:47.881 --> 11:49.099
SO DOES EVERYONE ELSE
ON THE PLANET.

11:49.143 --> 11:50.622
NO, IT'S LIKE
WE'RE NOT EVEN HERE.

11:50.666 --> 11:51.623
HEY, GUYS.

11:51.667 --> 11:52.929
HEY, THERE'S FOUR
OF US HERE.

11:52.973 --> 11:54.148
SO LET'S TRY TO--
OH.

11:54.191 --> 11:55.845
SORRY.OH, IT'S OKAY.

11:55.889 --> 11:58.152
DANNY WAS JUST
HELPING ME

11:58.195 --> 12:00.154
FIGURE OUT WHERE I SHOULD GET
MY FIRST TATTOO.

12:00.197 --> 12:01.068
UH-OH.
[clears throat]

12:01.111 --> 12:03.374
UM, YOU HATE TATTOOS.

12:03.418 --> 12:04.636
I DON'T THINK SO.

12:04.680 --> 12:06.508
I THINK I'M GONNA GET
A TATTOO AS WELL.

12:06.551 --> 12:08.075
A LITTLE BUTTERFLY
ON THE NAPE OF MY NECK,

12:08.118 --> 12:09.859
AND IT WOULD SIGNIFY
THAT I'M A FREE SPIRIT--

12:09.903 --> 12:11.165
WHAT TATTOO
ARE YOU GONNA GET?

12:11.208 --> 12:12.209
WELL,

12:12.253 --> 12:14.124
I THINK I SHOULD
KEEP IT A SECRET,

12:14.168 --> 12:15.212
BECAUSE WHERE I WANT
TO GET IT,

12:15.256 --> 12:16.779
ONLY CERTAIN PEOPLE
WOULD SEE IT.

12:16.823 --> 12:19.260
I-I DON'T KNOW, LUCE.

12:19.303 --> 12:21.305
I WORRY THAT A TATTOO IS A LITTLE SHORT-SIGHTED.

12:21.349 --> 12:23.264
YOU KNOW?MMM. CAN I TRY THAT?

12:23.307 --> 12:24.482
IS YOUR GRANDSON
REALLY GONNA UNDERSTAND

12:24.526 --> 12:26.310
WHY YOU HAVE A RADIOHEAD LYRIC

12:26.354 --> 12:27.659
UNDER YOUR BELLY BUTTON?

12:27.703 --> 12:28.791
I CAN'T UNDERSTAND
RADIOHEAD NOW.

12:28.835 --> 12:30.097
MMM!

12:30.140 --> 12:32.316
DO YOU WANNA HAVE SOME
OF MY COD?

12:32.360 --> 12:34.101
I'M FINE.
I JUST HAD SOME.

12:34.144 --> 12:36.886
WOW, THAT LAMB
IS SO, MMM, SUCCULENT.

12:36.930 --> 12:38.192
[Danny]
IT IS SUCCULENT.

12:38.235 --> 12:40.020
YOU ARE SUCH A GOOD ORDERER.THANK YOU.

12:40.063 --> 12:41.630
PICK A GOOD RESTAURANT,
AND THEY SAY, YOU KNOW,

12:41.673 --> 12:42.805
THE FOOD
ORDERS ITSELF, SO...

12:42.849 --> 12:45.329
MMM, TRY THIS.
OKAY.

12:45.373 --> 12:46.722
OH, OH, OH, OH, OH!
LUCY!

12:46.766 --> 12:48.289
YOUR COLD.
HMM?

12:48.332 --> 12:49.290
SHE HAD THIS HORRIBLE COLD
LAST WEEK.

12:49.333 --> 12:50.334
I'M GOOD WITH IT.
I'LL TAKE IT.

12:50.378 --> 12:51.640
YOU MIGHT
GET SOMETHING.

12:51.683 --> 12:53.163
I'M NOT SICK.
DO YOU WANT SOME OF MY COD?

12:53.207 --> 12:54.425
I DON'T GET SICK THAT OFTEN. I DON'T HAVE A COLD.

12:54.469 --> 12:55.426
YOU DON'T?
NO.

12:55.470 --> 12:56.732
EAT OFF MY FORK.
IT'S ROMANTIC.

12:56.776 --> 12:58.212
I DON'T NEED IT.
I'M NOT HUNGRY.

12:58.255 --> 13:00.301
EAT OFF MY FORK, PLEASE.

13:00.344 --> 13:01.650
ISN'T THAT GOOD?

13:01.693 --> 13:03.783
[choking]

13:03.826 --> 13:04.827
YOU ALL RIGHT, BUDDY?

13:04.871 --> 13:06.437
IT WAS JUST
A LITTLE PIECE OF COD.

13:06.481 --> 13:07.830
I'M SO SORRY.IT'S GOT BONES IN IT.
THAT'S WHY.

13:07.874 --> 13:08.918
HEY, JAMIE? ARE YOU GOOD?

13:08.962 --> 13:10.050
YOU CHOKING, BUDDY?

13:10.093 --> 13:11.355
THEY'RE DOCTORS.
YOU SHOULD JUST--

13:11.399 --> 13:12.313
OKAY?
[mouths words]

13:12.356 --> 13:14.184
YOU SURE?

13:14.228 --> 13:15.620
I'M GONNA-- IT HAS BONES IN IT.

13:15.664 --> 13:16.665
I CAN HEIMLICH. I KNOW.
PLEASE LET ME HEIMLICH YOU.

13:16.708 --> 13:18.275
[Mindy]
OKAY.

13:18.319 --> 13:20.538
I'M NOT GONNA LET YOU DIE
IN THIS WEIRD RESTAURANT, JAMIE.

13:20.582 --> 13:22.018
SHOULD WE GET DESSERT?

13:22.062 --> 13:23.846
[Danny]
I THINK HE'S CHOKING.

13:23.890 --> 13:25.500
[Lucy]
NO, HE'S OKAY.[all gasp]

13:25.543 --> 13:26.849
JAMIE, STOP![grunting]

13:26.893 --> 13:27.981
JAMIE!

13:28.024 --> 13:29.156
OH.OH, BOY.

13:29.199 --> 13:31.549
JAMIE, PLEASE STOP
DOING THAT!

13:31.593 --> 13:33.247
HEY, GUYS,
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

13:33.290 --> 13:34.509
SHE'S A DOCTOR.
SHE'S GOT IT.

13:34.552 --> 13:37.860
[choking]

13:41.472 --> 13:42.996
I JUST DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHY, IN 2013,

13:43.039 --> 13:44.475
RESTAURANTS HAVE ANY BONES
IN THEIR FISH.

13:44.519 --> 13:46.129
AND WHILE I APPRECIATE
THE GIFT CERTIFICATE

13:46.173 --> 13:47.435
AS A GESTURE,

13:47.478 --> 13:48.871
I DID THINK THE MANAGER
WAS PASSIVE-AGGRESSIVE,

13:48.915 --> 13:49.916
THE WAY THAT HE GAVE IT.

13:49.959 --> 13:50.960
YOU REMEMBER THAT?

13:51.004 --> 13:52.222
HEY, YOU KNOW WHAT?

13:52.266 --> 13:54.007
I THINK I'M GONNA
CALL IT A NIGHT, JAMIE.

13:54.050 --> 13:55.138
YOU ALMOST DIED.

13:55.182 --> 13:57.010
MY SHOES ARE PINCHING ME.

13:57.053 --> 13:58.750
SO--
NO. NO. NO.

13:58.794 --> 14:00.100
WE'RE GONNA CONTINUE
THIS DATE.

14:00.143 --> 14:02.711
I AM GONNA TAKE YOU
TO THE MOST ROMANTIC PLACE

14:02.754 --> 14:04.234
IN ALL OF NEW YORK CITY.

14:04.278 --> 14:06.323
AND POSSIBLY THE WORLD.

14:06.367 --> 14:08.543
[man]
KEEP MOVING, GUYS.

14:08.586 --> 14:11.198
PLEASE,
KEEP THE LINE MOVING.

14:11.241 --> 14:13.069
JAMIE, I CANNOT BELIEVE
YOU TOOK ME

14:13.113 --> 14:15.985
TO THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING
FOR VALENTINE'S DAY.

14:16.029 --> 14:17.595
LAST YEAR,
THE GUY I WAS WITH,

14:17.639 --> 14:18.945
HE TOOK ME
TO AN INDIAN CASINO,

14:18.988 --> 14:20.294
AND I LOST $2,000.

14:20.337 --> 14:21.817
[chuckles]
WELL, THIS IS ACTUALLY

14:21.861 --> 14:23.079
SOMETHING I'VE
ALWAYS WANTED TO DO.

14:23.123 --> 14:25.690
AND I FIGURED I'D COME
WITH THE PERFECT PERSON

14:25.734 --> 14:26.778
ON THE PERFECT NIGHT.

14:26.822 --> 14:27.779
[elevator dings]

14:27.823 --> 14:29.781
NEXT, PLEASE.

14:29.825 --> 14:31.218
WAIT, WAIT. JAMIE.

14:31.261 --> 14:33.916
UM, BEFORE WE GO
INTO THE MOST ROMANTIC BUILDING

14:33.960 --> 14:35.352
ON THE ENTIRE PLANET...
YEAH.

14:35.396 --> 14:36.658
CAN YOU JUST TELL ME
ONE THING?
YEAH.

14:36.701 --> 14:39.661
JUST--YOU'RE NOT IN LOVE
WITH LUCY, ARE YOU?

14:39.704 --> 14:40.792
NEXT, PLEASE.

14:40.836 --> 14:42.011
WHY DO YOU KEEP SAYING
THINGS LIKE THAT?

14:42.055 --> 14:44.013
IT JUST SEEMS LIKE
YOU WERE REALLY JEALOUS

14:44.057 --> 14:45.058
OF HER AND DANNY
AT DINNER.

14:45.101 --> 14:46.668
OKAY, I'M NOT JEALOUS
OF A GUY

14:46.711 --> 14:47.974
WHO WEARS BOOT CUT JEANS,
ALL RIGHT?

14:48.017 --> 14:48.931
SEE? THAT SOUNDS JEALOUS.

14:48.975 --> 14:50.411
LUCY IS MY BEST FRIEND.

14:50.454 --> 14:51.716
NEXT.AND IF I LOVE HER,

14:51.760 --> 14:53.196
IT'S THE WAY I WOULD LOVE
A SISTER.

14:53.240 --> 14:55.590
I HAVE A BROTHER, AND IF RISHI
LOOKED AT ME THAT WAY,

14:55.633 --> 14:56.852
I WOULD HAVE TO TALK
TO OUR DAD.

14:56.896 --> 14:58.419
NEXT, NEXT!

14:58.462 --> 14:59.899
LET'S GO, LADY.
COME ON.

14:59.942 --> 15:01.204
OKAY, WE'RE TRYING TO SORT
SOMETHING OUT RIGHT NOW.

15:01.248 --> 15:02.249
ALL RIGHT? CAN YOU JUST GIVE ME
A BREAK HERE?

15:02.292 --> 15:03.728
JUST LOOK
INTO YOUR LOVER'S EYES.

15:03.772 --> 15:05.208
IT'S VALENTINE'S DAY,
FOR GOD'S SAKE.COME ON.

15:05.252 --> 15:06.557
QUICK SCENARIO, OKAY?

15:06.601 --> 15:08.951
YOU ARE ON DEATH ROW
BECAUSE YOU MURDERED A COP.

15:08.995 --> 15:10.866
WHAT?
THIS IS HYPOTHETICAL.

15:10.910 --> 15:12.259
YOU CAN ONLY SEE ONE MORE PERSON
BEFORE THEY ELECTROCUTE YOU.

15:12.302 --> 15:13.260
WHO WOULD IT BE?

15:13.303 --> 15:14.435
MY LAWYER

15:14.478 --> 15:15.784
BECAUSE I WOULDN'T DO
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

15:15.827 --> 15:17.090
OKAY, YOUR LAWYER
BUNGLED THE CASE,

15:17.133 --> 15:19.266
AND YOU HAVE ONE PERSON
TO SEE BEFORE YOU DIE.

15:19.309 --> 15:22.095
YOU CAN SAY ME
IF IT'S ME.

15:27.709 --> 15:30.973
IT'S LUCY.

15:31.017 --> 15:32.192
I KNEW IT.

15:32.235 --> 15:33.280
YOU'RE GOOD AT THIS.

15:33.323 --> 15:34.759
IT'S LUCY!

15:34.803 --> 15:36.544
I'M IN LOVE WITH LUCY!

15:36.587 --> 15:38.415
[crowd exclaiming happily]

15:38.459 --> 15:39.721
NO, NO, NO, IT'S OKAY.
DON'T--

15:39.764 --> 15:40.940
I'M NOT LUCY.

15:40.983 --> 15:42.115
[all groaning sadly]

15:42.158 --> 15:43.159
NO, I MEAN, IT'S NOT--

15:43.203 --> 15:44.160
IT'S NOT, LIKE,
TRAUMATIZING.

15:44.204 --> 15:45.640
IT'S OKAY. IT'S NOT--

15:45.683 --> 15:46.728
IT'S JUST--
I'M OKAY WITH IT.

15:46.771 --> 15:48.382
[crowd murmuring]

15:48.425 --> 15:49.861
OKAY, FOLKS. NEXT.

15:49.905 --> 15:51.254
COME ON, LET'S GO.

15:51.298 --> 15:54.083
I'M A MAN IN LOVE!

15:54.127 --> 15:56.129
[groans]OH, MY GOD!

15:56.172 --> 15:57.304
JAMIE!

15:57.347 --> 15:58.914
THIS HAS NOT BEEN
A GOOD DAY FOR YOU.

15:58.958 --> 16:00.089
OKAY, ALL RIGHT.

16:00.133 --> 16:00.916
THAT'S IT, MORGAN.

16:00.960 --> 16:03.658
CASUAL APPROACH.

16:03.701 --> 16:04.572
OKAY, GOOD.

16:04.615 --> 16:06.095
NOW SOME LIGHT CONTACT.

16:06.139 --> 16:08.358
LIGHT.

16:08.402 --> 16:09.620
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

16:09.664 --> 16:11.361
MORGAN, HUMAN TOUCHING,
NOT DOG TOUCHING.

16:11.405 --> 16:13.189
AGH.

16:13.233 --> 16:16.149
GOOD--GOOD--
GOOD RECOVERY, I GUESS.

16:16.192 --> 16:17.802
NOW PARTING GIFT,
PARTING GIFT.

16:17.846 --> 16:19.587
COME ON, MORGAN.
COME ON.

16:19.630 --> 16:21.893
OH, HE FOUND THE BODY.

16:21.937 --> 16:24.200
SHE'S INTO IT.
WHO KNEW? OKAY.

16:24.244 --> 16:25.636
I--IT WORKED!

16:25.680 --> 16:27.682
BRAVO, MORGAN!
BRAVO.

16:27.725 --> 16:30.119
HEY, MAN,
I'M WORKING HERE.
SORRY.

16:31.381 --> 16:33.035
YOU FINALLY CAME
FOR ME, LOVE!

16:33.079 --> 16:34.906
OKAY, SHH.YOU FINALLY CALLED MY NAME!

16:34.950 --> 16:36.256
SHH. COME ON, COME ON.

16:36.299 --> 16:37.822
YOU'RE GONNA WAKE UP
MY NEIGHBORS.

16:37.866 --> 16:39.824
I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS IS
ALL BECAUSE OF YOU.

16:39.868 --> 16:40.825
YOU SHOWED ME THAT LOVE

16:40.869 --> 16:42.523
WAS RIGHT IN FRONT

16:42.566 --> 16:43.654
OF MY FACE.

16:43.698 --> 16:44.873
ALL RIGHT,
THAT'S SO GREAT.

16:44.916 --> 16:46.570
I NEVER THOUGHT I WOULD FEEL
THIS WAY, MINDY.

16:46.614 --> 16:47.702
WE CAN JUST WALK. IT IS GREAT.

16:47.745 --> 16:48.920
AND NOT DANCE AND STUFF.

16:48.964 --> 16:50.574
I'VE NEVER DONE
ANYTHING LIKE THIS.

16:50.618 --> 16:51.793
[slosh]
OKAY.

16:51.836 --> 16:52.881
THE WHOLE TIME.DISGUSTING, WATER ON MY--

16:52.924 --> 16:53.925
IT'S ALL BECAUSE OF YOU.

16:53.969 --> 16:55.797
YOU ARE SUCH
AN IMPORTANT CHARACTER

16:55.840 --> 16:56.885
IN THE STORY
OF LUCY AND ME.

16:56.928 --> 16:58.669
DON'T YOU REALIZE THAT?

16:58.713 --> 16:59.844
YEAH.
YOU'RE FATE'S HELPER.

16:59.888 --> 17:01.455
I'M LIKE
THE JOAN CUSACK CHARACTER

17:01.498 --> 17:03.848
IN THE ROMANTIC COMEDY
OF YOUR LIFE, YEAH.

17:03.892 --> 17:05.372
YES!
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

17:05.415 --> 17:06.677
CAN YOU BELIEVE
THIS IS ME?

17:06.721 --> 17:07.809
PEOPLE ARE GONNA THINK
YOU'RE ON DRUGS.

17:07.852 --> 17:09.071
I'M IN LOVE!
STOP IT, JAMIE.

17:09.115 --> 17:11.726
I'M FLYING.

17:13.597 --> 17:15.556
OH, MY GOD.

17:18.037 --> 17:20.039
HEY! WHAT THE HELL,
YOU GUYS?

17:20.082 --> 17:21.649
HEY, WHAT'S GOING ON,
LOVE BIRDS?

17:21.692 --> 17:23.085
ACTUALLY,
WE KIND OF BROKE UP.

17:23.129 --> 17:25.305
AND, FOR THE RECORD,
THERE IS NO KISSING ON MY STOOP.

17:25.348 --> 17:27.089
THAT IS A DIRECT QUOTE
FROM MY SUPER.

17:27.133 --> 17:28.656
OKAY, WELL, I LEFT MY GLOVES
AT YOUR PLACE.

17:28.699 --> 17:30.092
SO I JUST CAME HERE
TO PICK THEM UP.

17:30.136 --> 17:32.094
DID YOU THINK YOU WOULD FIND
THEM INSIDE OF HER MOUTH?

17:32.138 --> 17:34.314
YOU'RE MAKING OUT
WITH THIS GUY?

17:34.357 --> 17:36.359
THIS GUY, THEY ASK
IF HE WANTED A COCKTAIL,

17:36.403 --> 17:37.534
AND HE ORDERED SHRIMP?

17:37.578 --> 17:40.189
WHY ARE YOU YELLING?BECAUSE I LOVE YOU!

17:42.539 --> 17:45.629
REALLY?

17:49.198 --> 17:50.243
OKAY, WAIT A MINUTE.

17:50.286 --> 17:51.722
I LOVE YOU TOO!

17:51.766 --> 17:53.594
WHOA, WHOA, GUYS, WE WERE
JUST KISSING A SECOND AGO.

17:53.637 --> 17:55.726
ALL RIGHT, I'M GONNA CALL IT
A NIGHT AND HEAD IN.

17:55.770 --> 17:57.163
PARDON ME.GOD, I'VE BEEN DREAMING
ABOUT THIS

17:57.206 --> 17:58.599
FOR 15 YEARS!

17:58.642 --> 18:00.296
OKAY, CAN I--WHAT MADE YOU
CHANGE YOUR MIND?

18:00.340 --> 18:01.515
CAN I SQUEEZE BY HERE?MY LIFE FLASHED
BEFORE MY EYES

18:01.558 --> 18:02.864
WHEN I WAS CHOKING.

18:02.907 --> 18:04.344
JUST--IT SUDDENLY
DAWNED ON ME.EXCUSE ME.

18:04.387 --> 18:05.736
NOT TO BE A STICKLER,

18:05.780 --> 18:06.998
BUT I-I WAS THE PERSON

18:07.042 --> 18:08.565
WHO HELPED MAKE IT
DAWN ON YOU.

18:08.609 --> 18:09.653
MINDY HELPED. SHE WAS LIKE
A SUPPORTING CHARACTER.

18:09.697 --> 18:10.915
OH, THANK YOU!

18:10.959 --> 18:12.439
LET'S TAKE A WALK.
LET'S JUST GET OUTTA HERE.

18:12.482 --> 18:14.136
THAT'S THE WEIRDEST THING
I'VE EVER SEEN.

18:14.180 --> 18:16.007
YOU KNOW, I FEEL LIKE IF I HAD
JUST WORN THE FIRST DRESS,

18:16.051 --> 18:17.487
THAT THIS WOULDN'T
HAVE BEEN THE SITUATION.

18:17.531 --> 18:20.534
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S THE PROBLEM.

18:20.577 --> 18:22.753
HEY, DR. REED.MORGAN.

18:22.797 --> 18:24.929
I'M GONNA GO PICK UP
THREE OR FOUR CALZONES

18:24.973 --> 18:26.714
AND CRAWL INTO BED.

18:26.757 --> 18:28.150
WHO AM I KIDDING?
IT'S GONNA BE FOUR.

18:28.194 --> 18:29.630
WHAT HAPPENED?
DID YOU STRIKE OUT?

18:29.673 --> 18:31.501
HA. MY FIRST SPORTS ANALOGY.

18:31.545 --> 18:32.720
I HAD HER RIGHT
WHERE I WANTED HER.

18:32.763 --> 18:33.808
AND THEN, BAM!

18:33.851 --> 18:36.158
SHE DUMPS ME
LITERALLY THE SECOND

18:36.202 --> 18:37.333
WE'RE FINISHED HAVING SEX.

18:37.377 --> 18:38.682
WHOA, WHOA, WAIT.

18:38.726 --> 18:40.031
WHAT--SEX?

18:40.075 --> 18:41.250
I DID EVERYTHING
YOU TOLD ME.

18:41.294 --> 18:42.295
I WAS PLAYING IT COOL.

18:42.338 --> 18:43.818
SHE PULLS ME
INTO A SUPPLY CLOSET.

18:43.861 --> 18:46.516
WE START HAVING SEX
IN FRONT OF A BUNCH OF MOPS.

18:46.560 --> 18:47.909
YOU GOT EXACTLY
WHAT YOU WANTED.

18:47.952 --> 18:50.129
I WANTED TO TAKE HER
TO THE BATTING CAGES.

18:50.172 --> 18:51.695
I MEAN, YOU GOT THE GOOD STUFF
WITHOUT THE BORING STUFF.

18:51.739 --> 18:52.740
HOME RUN.

18:52.783 --> 18:53.871
DID IT AGAIN.

18:53.915 --> 18:55.786
THE BATTING CAGES
IS THE GOOD STUFF.

18:55.830 --> 18:58.137
I DON'T WANT TO HAVE SEX
WITH SOMEONE I CARE ABOUT

18:58.180 --> 18:59.181
IN A MOP CLOSET.

18:59.225 --> 19:00.835
I WANT TO DO IT
THE RIGHT WAY.

19:00.878 --> 19:02.053
ON THE COUCH,
IN THE LIVING ROOM,

19:02.097 --> 19:03.142
AFTER GRANDMOTHER'S ASLEEP.

19:03.185 --> 19:05.144
MORGAN, I'M SO SORRY.

19:05.187 --> 19:06.319
I NEED TO MAKE THIS
UP TO YOU.

19:06.362 --> 19:08.799
I FEEL LIKE
I'VE LED YOU ASTRAY.

19:08.843 --> 19:09.757
A STRAY?

19:09.800 --> 19:11.585
WHERE IS HE?
[groans]

19:11.628 --> 19:12.847
WE'RE GONNA FIND HIM.

19:12.890 --> 19:16.633
HOW'D HE GET IN THE BUILDING?
[whistles]

19:16.677 --> 19:17.808
ANOTHER ONE,
ANOTHER ONE.

19:17.852 --> 19:19.070
YOU GOTTA CHOKE UP.
DON'T GET TIRED.

19:19.114 --> 19:21.464
YOU CAN'T QUIT.
WE DON'T QUIT IN AMERICA.

19:21.508 --> 19:22.770
WHOA.

19:22.813 --> 19:23.988
CHECK ON THAT, MORGAN.

19:24.032 --> 19:26.208
SHOW ME HOW YOU DID
THAT WEIRD SWING.

19:26.252 --> 19:28.384
I WANT TO TRY THAT.
THAT'S PRETTY BAD-ASS.

19:28.428 --> 19:30.212
YOU GOT, LIKE, A MICHAEL CAINE,
GARY SHEFFIELD--

19:30.256 --> 19:31.474
OH! OH, GOD!

19:31.518 --> 19:32.736
RIGHT IN THE CAR KEYS.

19:32.780 --> 19:34.999
OH! OH, HO, HO!

19:35.043 --> 19:37.306
OH!
[sobbing]

19:37.350 --> 19:39.743
DANNY, I WAS THIS CLOSE

19:39.787 --> 19:41.876
TO SPENDING VALENTINE'S DAY
AT THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING.

19:41.919 --> 19:43.269
TO PUT THAT IN YOU TERMS,

19:43.312 --> 19:44.574
THAT'S LIKE LOSING
YOUR VIRGINITY

19:44.618 --> 19:45.662
AT YANKEE STADIUM.

19:45.706 --> 19:46.924
SEE, THAT'S YOUR PROBLEM.

19:46.968 --> 19:48.448
YEAH, NO, THAT'S WHAT
I'M DOING, DANNY.

19:48.491 --> 19:49.884
I'M DESCRIBING MY PROBLEM.

19:49.927 --> 19:51.973
WHO TOLD YOU THE EMPIRE STATE
BUILDING WAS ROMANTIC?

19:52.016 --> 19:53.844
A POSTCARD
AT THE AIRPORT GIFT SHOP?

19:53.888 --> 19:55.759
SOME DUMB MOVIE
WITH TOM HANKS

19:55.803 --> 19:57.848
WHERE HE'S HUGGING IN THE RAIN
AND THERE'S NO UMBRELLAS?

19:57.892 --> 19:59.937
YOU KNOW WHAT?
COME HERE.

19:59.981 --> 20:01.025
I WANT TO SHOW YOU SOMETHING.

20:01.069 --> 20:04.290
[big band music playing]

20:04.333 --> 20:05.421
THIS IS IT.

20:05.465 --> 20:06.727
OH, COOL.

20:06.770 --> 20:09.120
YOUR FAVORITE PIZZA PLACE.

20:09.164 --> 20:11.035
YEAH, DANNY,
THIS DOES CHEER ME UP.

20:11.079 --> 20:12.689
OKAY, I'M READY TO GO.NO, NO, NO.

20:12.733 --> 20:14.517
I WANT TO SHOW YOU SOMETHING.
SIT DOWN.

20:14.561 --> 20:16.476
SAL, CAN WE GET TWO SLICES? YOU GOT IT.

20:16.519 --> 20:18.521
THIS, LIKE, A SETTING
FROM GOODFELLASOR SOMETHING?

20:18.565 --> 20:20.871
NO, THIS IS
WHERE I MET MY WIFE.

20:20.915 --> 20:22.046
WHAT?
YEP.

20:22.090 --> 20:23.831
HERE?
YEAH. CHECK THIS OUT.

20:23.874 --> 20:24.832
I WANNA SHOW YOU THIS.

20:24.875 --> 20:26.225
[gasps]

20:26.268 --> 20:27.443
DANNY, YOU LITTLE FELON.

20:27.487 --> 20:30.054
THAT'S AWESOME.
HER NAME WAS CHRISTINA?

20:30.098 --> 20:31.055
YEP.

20:31.099 --> 20:32.056
WERE YOU EVER LIKE...

20:32.100 --> 20:33.057
[Italian accent]
"EH, CHRISTINA,

20:33.101 --> 20:36.147
I LOVE YOU SO MUCH-A."

20:36.191 --> 20:37.540
YEAH.

20:37.584 --> 20:39.716
OH.

20:39.760 --> 20:41.152
[chuckles]

20:41.196 --> 20:43.807
I THINK I STILL
REALLY MISS HER.

20:43.851 --> 20:45.026
WELL, NOW YOU CAN--

20:45.069 --> 20:46.332
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

20:46.375 --> 20:47.333
WHY DO YOU NEED
TO TAKE A PICTURE OF EVERYTHING?

20:47.376 --> 20:48.595
SO THAT YOU ALWAYS
REMEMBER IT

20:48.638 --> 20:49.596
AND YOU NEVER FORGET.

20:49.639 --> 20:51.293
STOP IT.I WANT TO SHOW MORGAN.

20:51.337 --> 20:52.381
NO, DON'T--

20:52.425 --> 20:53.730
WE CAN TELL HIM
ABOUT IT, OKAY?

20:53.774 --> 20:55.515
LOOK, LOOK, THE MOST ROMANTIC
PLACE IN THE WORLD,

20:55.558 --> 20:57.778
YOU DON'T KNOW IT'S GONNA BE
ROMANTIC AHEAD OF TIME.

20:57.821 --> 20:59.388
LIKE, FOR YOU,
IT COULD BE ANYWHERE.

20:59.432 --> 21:01.477
LIKE A BARBERSHOP

21:01.521 --> 21:04.001
OR AN ATM SHELTER

21:04.045 --> 21:05.307
OR H&R BLOCK.

21:05.351 --> 21:07.309
DANNY, I'M PRETTY SURE
IT'S GONNA BE

21:07.353 --> 21:08.615
THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING,

21:08.658 --> 21:10.138
BUT THOSE ARE
VERY CUTE SUGGESTIONS.

21:10.181 --> 21:11.966
BY THE WAY, EYE PATCH
WAS WRONG ABOUT YOU.

21:12.009 --> 21:13.576
YOU'RE NOT MEAN.

21:13.620 --> 21:15.099
SHE JUST DIDN'T KNOW YOU
WELL ENOUGH.

21:15.143 --> 21:16.449
THERE YOU GO, DANNY.

21:16.492 --> 21:19.321
THANK YOU.
THANKS.

21:19.365 --> 21:20.453
THANKS.

21:20.496 --> 21:21.541
HEY, HOW THE--
HOW IS THE PIZZA HERE?

21:21.584 --> 21:22.759
WORST PIZZA
IN THE CITY.

21:22.803 --> 21:24.326
OH.

21:24.370 --> 21:27.851
HAPPY VALENTINE'S DAY.HAPPY VALENTINE'S DAY.

21:27.895 --> 21:30.463
JUST WANT TO TAKE
ONLY THE CRUST.

21:30.506 --> 21:32.334
THE CRUST
IS MY FAVORITE PART.

21:32.378 --> 21:34.336
YOU'RE SO WEIRD.

21:34.380 --> 21:36.469
[man]
GO TO BED.
